    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n391" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀίω</span></b>  (1) (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀϝίω</span>), only pres. and ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄιον</span>: (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hear;</span> abs., and w. gen. or acc.
          —(2) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">mark, perceive</span>, never inconsistently with the
          sense of <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hearing</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πληγῆς
            ἀίοντες</span>, the horses hear the lash as well as feel the
          stroke, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.532</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">.— οὐκ ἀίεις</span> (=<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀκούεις</span>;); or, sometimes, ‘markest thou not?’
          ‘remarkest,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 15.248</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.298</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
